209300171119Wildcard character - Hilfe
209400171119:XH3.Wildcard character (WILDCARD)
209500171119:P.
209600171119Specifies the character that is used as the wildcard character when
209700171119searching for and replacing string.
209800171119:P.
209900171119The wildcard character is used to substitute any character in the search
210000171119argument when comparing string. For example when searching for
210100171119:HP2.?oat:EHP2. :HP2.boat:EHP2. is found but also also :HP2.coat:EHP2.
210200171119and :HP2.goat:EHP2..
210300171119:P.
210400171119When used in the replacement string the wildcard character is used
210500171119to preserve characters of the source string. If for example
210600171119:HP2.UTF-8:EHP2. shall be replaced by :HP2.UTF-16:EHP2. preserving
210700171119the case of :HP2.UTF:EHP2., the replacement string has to be specified
210800171119as :HP2.???-16:EHP2. when using the question mark (?) as
210900171119the wildcard character.
211000171119.*
211100171119:IMHELP name='COM/OPTPARM'.
211200171119.*
211300171119:PARML.
211400171119:PT.:PK DEF.*NONE:EPK.
211500171119:PD.Specify *NONE to search and replace without using a
211600171119wildcard character.
211700171119:PT.:PV.wildcard-character:EPV.
211800171119:PD.Specify a character to use as the wildcard.
211900171119:EPARML.
